n%20the%20latest%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fthe-equity-talk%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EEquity%20Talk%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%2C%20Doria%20opens%20up%20about%20when%2C%20and%20how%2C%20she%20stood%20up%20for%20herself.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDoria%20said%20asking%20the%20right%20questions%20as%20a%20leader%20matters.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Myra%20Doria%20was%2010%20years%20old%2C%20she%20used%20to%20sell%20clothes%20and%20shoes%20at%20a%20local%20flea%20market%20in%20the%20Philippines.%20She%20learned%20about%20strategy%2C%20the%20customer%2C%20pricing%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Bbeing%20better%20than%20yesterday.%26quot%3B%20You%20might%20say%20sales%20is%20in%20her%20DNA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20those%20early%20days%2C%20all%20Doria%20wanted%20was%20shoes%2C%20but%20she%20never%20had%20enough%20money.%20%26quot%3BI%20told%20myself%20someday%20I%20will%20buy%20so%20many%20pairs%20of%20shoes%20because%20I%20love%20them.%26quot%3B%20Today%2C%20she%20has%20300%20pairs%20and%20%26quot%3BI%20tell%20my%20story%20about%20shoes%20because%20shoes%20keep%20me%20grounded%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoria%20said%20shoes%20always%20point%20forward%2C%20toward%20the%20future.%20They%20can%20be%20%26quot%3Ba%20bit%20tough%2C%20but%20they%20become%20better%20when%20you%20wear%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20they%20allow%20her%20to%20have%20a%20positive%20footprint%20on%20the%20lives%20of%20those%20who%20work%20for%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoria%20became%20McDonald's%20USA%20national%20field%20president%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20and%20is%20responsible%20for%20more%20than%2013%2C000%20restaurants%20and%20for%20leading%20strategy%2C%20brand%20development%2C%20and%20talent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoria%20told%20me%2C%20%26quot%3Bthis%20was%20a%20proud%20moment%20for%20me%20because%20I%20broke%20the%20bamboo%20ceiling.%20I%20call%20it%20the%20bamboo%20ceiling%20because%20the%20glass%20ceiling%20is%20easier%20to%20break%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20throw%20a%20stone%20and%20it's%20on%20a%20glass%20ceiling%2C%20it%20will%20break.%20The%20bamboo%20ceiling%2C%20you%20throw%20a%20stone%20it's%20gonna%20go%20back%20to%20you%20because%20the%20pliability%20of%20that%20how%20it's%20made%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoria%2C%20whose%20favorite%20McDonald's%20meal%20is%20chicken%20McNuggets%20with%20honey%20mustard%2C%20spoke%20to%20Insider%20about%20her%20leadership%20journey%20at%20the%20storied%20fast-food%20company.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20through%20my%20journey%20through%20McDonald's%2C%20it's%20not%20been%20easy%2C%20but%20it's%20been%20so%20rewarding.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20following%20interview%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAs%20a%20woman%20of%20color%20the%20journey%20isn't%20easy.%20I%20know%20for%20myself%2C%20there%20have%20been%20difficult%20moments.%20How%20has%20your%20journey%20been%3F%20And%20if%20there%20was%20a%20difficult%20moment%2C%20how%20did%20you%20handle%20it%20and%20overcome%20it%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20instances%20where%20I%20had%20to%20stand%20up%20for%20myself.%20So%20there%20was%20a%20time%20in%20my%20career%20when%20someone%20had%20told%20me%2C%20this%20will%20be%20your%20last%20role%20in%20the%20company.%20You%20will%20never%20be%20an%20officer%20of%20McDonald's.%20And%20that%20kind%20of%20took%20me%20aback%20because%20I%20want%20to%20lead%20in%20a%20bigger%20way.%20I%20want%20to%20be%20a%20vice%20president%20for%20the%20company%2C%20because%20I%20know%20I%20am%20capable.%20That%20person%20who%20was%20my%20boss%20at%20that%20time%20told%20me%20that%20and%20I%20was%20surprised.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20every%20moment%20that%20I%20experienced%20in%20that%20way%2C%20I%20have%20to%20pick%20up%20myself.%20I've%20learned%20what%20the%20role%20is.%20I%20did%20a%20great%20job%20in%20my%20current%20role.%20I%20had%20mentors%20around%20me%20who%20had%20given%20me%20so%20much%20counsel%20and%20coaching%20along%20the%20way.%20I%20also%20made%20sure%20that%20I%20show%20up%20in%20a%20big%20way%2C%20in%20terms%20of%20what%20the%20future%20role%20is%20going%20to%20be%20and%20how%20I'm%20capable%20of%20doing%20it%20on%20my%20current%20role%20at%20that%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22574%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22McDonald's%20USA%20National%20Field%20President%2C%20Myra%20Doria%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65302637211def8ed83864c7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22384%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMcDonald's%20USA%20National%20Field%20President%2C%20Myra%20Doria.%3Cp%3EMcDonald's%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20tell%20myself%2C%20no%20one%20will%20tell%20me%20that%20I%20can't.%20The%20only%20person%20who%20can%20tell%20me%20who%20I%20am%20is%20just%20myself%20because%20I've%20given%20up.%20But%20through%20those%20I%20actually%20tell%20the%20story%20all%20the%20time%20to%20inspire%20others.%20That%20you%20can%20dream%20big%2C%20and%20you%20can%20accomplish%20what%20you%20want%20to%20accomplish.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20situation%20is%20when%20you%20grow%20up%20at%20a%20company%20where%20you%20are%20the%20only%20woman%20in%20a%20room.%20And%20as%20I%20shared%20with%20you%20that%20I%20grew%20up%20in%20an%20Asian%20culture%20where%20you%20are%20not%20allowed%20to%20answer%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20never%20answer%20back%2C%20you%20know%20to%20my%20parents%2C%20or%20anyone%20senior%20than%20me%2C%20that%20was%20the%20culture%20I%20was%20brought%20up.%20But%20in%20the%20McDonald's%20culture%2C%20they%20told%20me%20that%20I%20didn't%20speak%20up%20enough%20in%20meetings%2C%20I%20didn't%20challenge%20others.%20%26quot%3BHow%20can%20we%20make%20you%20a%20manager%20when%20you're%20so%20quiet%3F%20You%20didn't%20talk%20in%20a%20meeting!%26quot%3B%20And%20I've%20learned%20it%20doesn't%20have%20to%20change%20my%20values%2C%20but%20it%20changed%20who%20I%20am%20as%20a%20leader%20and%20how%20I%20show%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20became%20more%20purposeful%20and%20when%20I%20speak%2C%20I%20want%20to%20make%20sure%20I%20speak%20with%20when%20I%20am%20passionate%20about%20an%20agenda.%20And%20I%20also%20ask%20for%20feedback%20on%20how%20did%20I%20show%20up%20in%20the%20meeting.%20You%20have%20to%20be%20thick-skinned%20to%20be%20able%20to%20accept%20those%20feedback%20that%20sometimes%20that%20feedback%20aren't%20always%20good%2C%20right%3F%20But%20it%20will%20make%20you%20a%20better%20leader.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat's%20your%20favorite%20thing%20about%20your%20job%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20favorite%20thing%20about%20my%20job%20is%20my%20impact%20on%20people.%20I%20have%20almost%201%2C000%20staff%20that%20I%20have%20in%20all%20the%20different%20field%20offices%20today%2C%20including%20the%20support%20team.%20I%20have%20seen%20them%20grow%20seeing%20them%20develop.%20This%20week%20I%20visited%20the%20San%20Antonio%20market%2C%20and%20we%20had%20a%20town%20hall%20meeting%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20our%20staff.%20And%20many%20of%20them%20I've%20seen%20they%20were%20general%20managers%20in%20restaurants%20before.%20Now%20they%20are%20directors.%20They%20were%20telling%20me%20my%20remember%20the%20coaching%20you've%20given%20us.%20McDonald's%20is%20about%20people.%20It's%20about%20the%20journey%20of%20talent.%20And%20that's%20what%20makes%20me%20so%20excited%20about%20my%20role%20and%20the%20more%20I%20can%20do%20far%20challenge%20across%20the%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20was%20the%20biggest%20thing%20on%20your%20to%20do%20list%20this%20year%20and%20have%20you%20accomplished%20it%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20biggest%20to-do%20was%20on%20the%20personal%20side%3A%20travel%20for%20my%20family.%20We've%20never%20really%20traveled%20together%20all%20the%20time.%20You%20know%2C%20my%20kids%20are%20all%20over%20the%20the%20US.%20So%20while%20we%20travel%20outside%20the%20US%20we%20went%20to%20another%20international%20country%20together%20during%20the%20summer.%20It%20was%20phenomenal.%20I%20got%20a%20chance%20to%20have%20meals%20with%20my%20kids%20to%20speak%20with%20them%20about%20their%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWork%20wise%2C%20my%20biggest%20thing%20this%20year%20that%20I%20wanted%20to%20accomplish%20is%20to%20be%20able%20to%20travel%20across%20the%20US%20to%20all%20the%2010%20field%20offices%2C%20sharing%20my%20vision%2C%20sharing%20what's%20important%2C%20and%20how%20do%20we%20get%20there.%20How%20do%20we%20develop%20talents%20across%20the%20system%2C%20listening%20to%20our%20people%20across%20the%2010%20field%20offices.%20And%20that's%20one%20of%20the%20big%20things%20I%20want%20to%20do%20when%20I%20was%20in%20one%20of%20the%20roles%20and%20I%20was%20able%20to%20do%20it%20%E2%80%94%20within%2090%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20you%20open%20new%20stores%20and%20franchises%2C%20how%20do%20you%20ensure%20they're%20diverse%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%20we%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcorporate.mcdonalds.com%2Fcorpmcd%2Four-stories%2Farticle%2Ffranchisee-diversity.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elaunched%20a%20campaign%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20attracting%20diverse%20franchisees%20across%20multiple%20different%20backgrounds%20across%20the%20globe%2C%20and%20in%20the%20US.%20As%20part%20of%20that%2C%20we%20allotted%20%24250%20million%20over%20five%20years%20in%20the%20US%20to%20provide%20alternatives%20to%20traditional%20financing.%20We%20have%20seen%20some%20socioeconomic%20difficulties%20to%20get%20into%20the%20business.%20As%20of%20the%20end%20of%202022%20new%20franchisees%20took%20advantage%20of%20more%20than%20%2450%20million%20in%20alternative%20financing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20now%20we%20are%20still%20kind%20of%20establishing%20that%20in%20the%20next%20five%2C%20four%20more%20years%2C%20because%20it's%20a%20five-year%20campaign%20in%20terms%20of%20this%20opportunity%20for%20attracting%20diverse%20franchisees%20across%20the%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E(The%20company%20recently%20shared%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mcdonalds.com%2Fus%2Fen-us%2Fnow-serving.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E1%20in%208%20Americans%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20worked%20at%20a%20McDonald's%20restaurant.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELet's%20touch%20on%20economic%20mobility.%20One%20thing%20that%20we%20see%20is%20that%20we%20do%20need%20to%20do%20some%20extra%20outreach%20for%20women%20or%20for%20younger%20generations%20or%20for%20people%20of%20color.%20How%20is%20that%20going%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20we%20have%20recruitment%20campaigns%20around%20McDonald's%2C%20and%20this%20is%20very%20grassroots%20efforts.%20So%20we%20go%20into%20communities%20where%20we%20have%20where%20we%20attract%20different%20diverse%20candidates.%20We%20have%2C%20you%20know%2C%20a%20sole%20person%20in%20charge%20of%20recruitment%20of%20different%20franchisees%20across%20the%20US%20in%20different%20socio%20economic%20environments.%20And%20we've%20done%20it%20for%20example%2C%20you%20know%2C%20but%20these%20are%20all%20good%20grassroots%20efforts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERight%20now%20there's%20a%20need%20for%20new%20franchisees%20in%20places%20across%20the%20Midwest%20and%20down%20through%20Texas.%20We%20have%20agencies%20that%20are%20helping%20us%20recruit%20within%20those%20areas%20through%20different%20business%20organizations.%20We%20also%20have%20a%20department%20that%20is%20dedicated%20to%20making%20sure%20those%20prospective%20franchisees%20can%20take%20advantage%20of%20the%20alternative%20financing%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20do%20you%20think%20the%20biggest%20challenge%20is%20to%20work%20life%20balance%20for%20working%20parents%20and%20how%20does%20McDonald's%20aim%20to%20support%20them%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20encourage%20people%20within%20our%20company%20to%20work%20in%20the%20office%20at%20least%20three%20times%20a%20week%20and%20they%20have%20flexibility%20on%20doing%20that.%20That%20helps%20a%20lot%20with%20taking%20care%20of%20your%20kids%20and%20and%20coordinating%20with%20your%20household.%20But%20the%20more%20we%20prioritize%20work%20the%20more%20we%20make%20sure%20that%20we%20are%20focusing%20on%20creating%20that%20flexibility%20within%20our%20system.%20It%20makes%20people%20more%20being%20able%20to%20adjust%20their%20schedule%20between%20family%20life%20and%20work-life%20balance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20also%20do%20something%20in%20our%20restaurants%2C%20actually%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20our%20restaurants%20our%20employees%20are%20part%20time%20and%20we%20offer%20so%20much%20flexibility%20within%20our%20restaurants%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20things%20people%20request%20is%20flexibility%20of%20schedule%2C%20and%20we%20want%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20we%20accommodate%20those%20hours%20that%20they%20want%20to%20work%20so%20we%20have%20availability%20of%20hours.%20We've%20also%20tested%20childcare%20options%20for%20our%20people%20and%20we%20will%20continue%20to%20test%20those%20to%20to%20give%20availability%20of%20childcare%20opportunity%20for%20those%20working%20parents%20that%20they%20can%20take%20advantage%20of%20those%20at%20a%20low%20cost%20so%20they%20can%20work%20at%20the%20same%20time%20and%20have%20their%20kids%20safe%20within%20those%20childcare%20facilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20the%20biggest%20change%20from%20the%20pandemic%20that%20you%20hope%20sticks%20in%20the%20workforce%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20lot%20of%20change%20right%20now%20people%20you%20know%2C%20even%20even%20with%20the%20mobility%20of%20our%20people%20across%20the%20system%2C%20there's%20more%20now%20people%20don't%20want%20to%20move%20right.%20They%20want%20to%20stay%20put%20and%20have%20family%20support.%20They've%20learned%20during%20the%20pandemic%20that%20all%20of%20t