C%20more%20people%20are%20forgoing%20coverage%20each%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20most%20people%2C%20private%20insurance%20is%20their%20primary%20source%20of%20security%20against%20the%20vast%20array%20of%20(un)known%20risks%20that%20threaten%20to%20upturn%20their%20lives.%20Even%20if%20you%20live%20outside%20the%20US%20and%20don't%20rely%20on%20private%20health%20insurers%2C%20you%20still%20need%20to%20purchase%20private%20insurance%20for%20your%20car%2C%20home%2C%20income%2C%20and%20life.%20Beyond%20that%2C%20there%20are%20extensive%20types%20of%20commercial%20insurance%20that%20underwrite%20finance%2C%20business%2C%20logistics%2C%20infrastructure%2C%20government%2C%20and%20everything%20else%20in%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20industry%20we%20depend%20upon%20as%20a%20bulwark%20against%20an%20uncertain%20world%20is%20also%20increasingly%20designed%20to%20screw%20us%20over.%20Instead%20of%20using%20new%20technologies%20like%20artificial%20intelligence%20to%20calculate%20a%20customer's%20precise%20risk%20and%20determine%20a%20fair%20rate%20for%20them%20to%20pay%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2F10.1177%2F03063127231186437%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einsurers%20are%20innovating%3C%2Fa%3E%20all%20kinds%20of%20new%20ways%20to%20undermine%20our%20security%20and%20juice%20their%20profits%20%E2%80%94%20all%20under%20the%20guise%20of%20convenience%20and%20objective-risk%20science.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EInsurance%20is%20supposed%20to%20make%20us%20feel%20safe%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20talk%20to%20insiders%20working%20in%20the%20industry%2C%20they%20readily%20(even%20too%20eagerly)%20admit%20that%20insurance%20is%20a%20grudge%20purchase.%20Consumers%20agree.%20Private%20insurers%20are%20among%20the%20least%20trusted%20industries%20by%20consumers%2C%20with%20health%20insurers%20being%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjacobin.com%2F2021%2F06%2Fus-health-care-medicare-insurance%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emost%20hated%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20noted%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F5127434.fs1.hubspotusercontent-na1.net%2Fhubfs%2F5127434%2FReport%2520Downloadables%2FFinancial%2520Services%2520Reputation%2520Report%25202023%2520-%2520Caliber.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Caliber%2C%20a%20reputation-management%20consultancy%2C%20consumers%20see%20insurance%20%26quot%3Bmore%20as%20a%20necessary%20evil%20than%20something%20that%20is%20largely%20value-driven.%26quot%3B%20That%20is%2C%20we%20see%20insurance%20as%20driven%20not%20by%20producing%20value%20for%20the%20public%20but%20by%20%26quot%3Bturning%20an%20enormous%20profit%20for%20shareholders%2C%26quot%3B%20S%C3%B8ren%20Holm%2C%20a%20senior%20advisor%20at%20Caliber%2C%20recently%20told%20the%20trade%20publication%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insurancebusinessmag.com%2Fus%2Fnews%2Flife-insurance%2Fsurvey-reveals-top-insurers-globally-for-consumer-trust-and-recognition-454682.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInsurance%20Business%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20insurance%20is%20a%20critical%20tool%20to%20make%20the%20world%20safer.%20By%20pooling%20risks%20among%20large%20groups%2C%20no%20one%20has%20to%20bear%20the%20full%20burden%20of%20health%20scares%20or%20random%20catastrophes%20on%20their%20own.%20That%20sense%20of%20social%20solidarity%20is%20why%20many%20early%20forms%20of%20insurance%20were%20tied%20to%20unions%2C%20guilds%2C%20and%20community%20groups.%20And%20it's%20why%20insurance%20is%20often%20mandated%20for%20things%20like%20driving%20a%20car%20or%20buying%20a%20house%3A%20It%20works%20better%20when%20everybody%20is%20in%20it%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday's%20insurers%20say%20they%20are%20selling%20%26quot%3Bpeace%20of%20mind%26quot%3B%20and%20hawk%20themselves%20as%20neighbors%20who%20are%20always%20there%20when%20you%20need%20them.%20But%20that%20sense%20of%20security%20does%20not%20ring%20true%20for%20people%20who%20feel%20cheated%20when%20insurers%20use%20a%20morass%20of%20loopholes%20and%20exclusions%20to%20deny%20claims%20while%20continuing%20to%20raise%20premiums%20or%20cancel%20policies%20altogether.%20For%20insurers%2C%20the%20best-case%20scenario%20is%20that%20they%20keep%20getting%20paid%20by%20customers%20who%20never%20face%20disaster%2C%20and%20therefore%20never%20need%20their%20insurance.%20So%20when%20the%20bills%20for%20a%20catastrophe%20come%20due%2C%20companies%20are%20not%20eager%20to%20pay%20out.%20Not%20so%20neighborly%20after%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBehind%20the%20curtain%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EInsurance%20is%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fadvisor%2Fcar-insurance%2Finsurance-policies-impossible-to-read%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eesoteric%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.propublica.org%2Farticle%2Fhow-to-appeal-insurance-denials-too-complicated%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebyzantine%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Finteractive%2F2021%2F08%2F22%2Fupshot%2Fhospital-prices.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esecretive%3C%2Fa%3E%20business%2C%20so%20most%20of%20us%20only%20see%20the%20tip%20of%20the%20iceberg%20%E2%80%94%20the%20rejected%20claims%2C%20the%20raised%20costs%2C%20the%20revoked%20coverage.%20What%20we%20don't%20see%20are%20the%20complex%20systems%20that%20insurers%20have%20created%20to%20keep%20us%20in%20the%20dark%2C%20collect%20as%20much%20data%20as%20possible%2C%20and%20squeeze%20profits%20from%20the%20customers%20they%20are%20meant%20to%20serve.%20And%20the%20further%20integration%20of%20technologies%20like%20AI%20is%20only%20supercharging%20the%20industry's%20capacity%20to%20rip%20us%20off%20while%20allowing%20companies%20to%20evade%20public%20awareness%20and%20accountability.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20years%20past%2C%20insurance%20policies%20were%20based%20largely%20on%20broad%20demographic%20categories%20like%20age%20and%20gender.%20Now%2C%20with%20the%20vast%20range%20of%20data%20insurers%20have%20access%20to%2C%20consumers%20are%20charged%20not%20just%20based%20on%20their%20objective%20risks%20but%20also%20based%20on%20how%20much%20they%20are%20willing%20to%20pay%20%E2%80%94%20a%20practice%20called%20price%20optimization.%20To%20make%20those%20predictions%2C%20insurers%20gather%20and%20analyze%20data%20about%20individuals%20to%20create%20detailed%20personal%20profiles%2C%20looking%20at%20everything%20from%20whether%20you%20smoke%20cigarettes%20to%20your%20shopping%20habits%20to%20which%20internet%20browser%20you%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Duncan%20Minty%2C%20an%20ethics%20consultant%20for%20insurers%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ethicsandinsurance.info%2Fa-legal-spotlight-turns-on-discrimination-in-claims%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecently%20wrote%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%26quot%3BIt's%20difficult%20to%20think%20of%20data%20that%20they%20haven't%20been%20collecting%20about%20policyholders.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20data%20is%20fed%20into%20proprietary%20models%20for%20analysis%20to%20determine%20how%20much%20to%20charge%20a%20particular%20consumer.%20The%20personalized%20prices%20that%20the%20algorithm%20spits%20out%20are%20not%20just%20based%20on%20how%20risky%20a%20person%20is%20compared%20to%20other%20similar%20people%20but%20also%20on%20metrics%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.the-digital-insurer.com%2Fcif-why-customer-lifetime-value-is-the-key-metric-every-digital-business-needs-to-focus-on-and-how-to-effectively-adopt-it-in-insurance%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECustomer%20Lifetime%20Value%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20or%20the%20predicted%20net%20profit%20that%20a%20customer%20will%20deliver%20over%20their%20lifetime.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20determine%20that%20magic%20price%20tag%2C%20insurance%20companies%20drill%20down%20into%20the%20nitty-gritty%20details%20of%20your%20life.%20They%20might%20look%20at%20your%20home's%20roof%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eagleview.com%2Finsurance%2Fdrone-roof-inspection-for-insurance-a-full-guide%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eusing%20drones%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20automated%20image%20analysis%2C%20or%20where%20you're%20driving%20based%20on%20data%20from%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.trustage.com%2Flearn%2Funderstanding-insurance%2Fhow-do-car-tracking-devices-work%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esmart%20device%20in%20your%20car%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20what%20kinds%20of%20foods%20you're%20eating%20by%20looking%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fiercehealthcare.com%2Fpayers%2Felevance-health-rolls-out-nutrition-tracker-its-sydney-member-app%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enutrition%20trackers%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20might%20also%20look%20at%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3Daa7bdc403463eaad9c0d63b8e8b7e7d3e5cf5904741789d03211963005a4e0bc%26postID%3D6531458fcb790ff8bec23092%26postSlug%3Dinsurance-companies-get-you-to-pay-more-deny-claims-2023-10%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.credible.com%252Fblog%252Fhome-insurance%252Finsurance-score%252F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecredit%20score%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rateforce.com%2Fblog%2Fauto-insurance%2Fdoes-zip-code-affect-car-insurance%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EZIP%20code%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fverdict.justia.com%2F2012%2F01%2F03%2Fwill-insurers-begin-to-use-social-media-postings-to-calculate-premiums%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esocial-media%20posts%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fwant-a-loan-in-china-keep-your-phone-charged-1491474250%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebattery-charging%20habits%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20data%20can%20then%20be%20used%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Filr.law.uiowa.edu%2Fprint%2Fvolume-105-issue-3%2Fproxy-discrimination-in-the-age-of-artificial-intelligence-and-big-data%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproxies%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20social%20categories%20like%20class%20and%20race%20or%20to%20make%20moral%20judgments%20about%20your%20personal%20responsibility%2C%20which%20factor%20into%20decisions%20for%20prices%20and%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20can%20now%20reveal%20things%20that%2C%20in%20the%20past%2C%20only%20God%20knew%20about%2C%20thanks%20to%20technology%20including%20AI%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20president%20of%20Sompo%20Holdings%2C%20one%20of%20Japan's%20largest%20insurance%20companies%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2Fa3372e1a-d43c-403e-97e5-449b50d51b87%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20last%20year%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInsurers%20justify%20possessing%20so%20much%20data%20by%20saying%20that%20it's%20all%20in%20the%20name%20of%20fairness.%20Everybody%20should%20be%20charged%20according%20to%20their%20own%20risk.%20The%20only%20way%20to%20know%20that%20fair%20price%20is%20for%20insurers%20to%20have%20a%20vast%20amount%20of%20information%20about%20each%20individual.%20But%20how%20exactly%20they%20reach%20those%20decisions%20is%20largely%20unexplained.%20We%20have%20to%20guess%2C%20piece%20things%20together%2C%20and%20reverse%20engineer%20the%20results.%20And%20the%20outcomes%20seem%20to%20always%20favor%20insurers%20above%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.policygenius.com%2Fauto-insurance%2Fhome-auto-technology-survey-2022%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20survey%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20most%20people%20are%20opposed%20to%20these%20kinds%20of%20surveillance%20programs%3A%20%26quot%3B68%25%20of%20Americans%20would%20not%20install%20an%20app%20that%20collects%20driving%20behavior%20or%20location%20data%20for%20any%20insurance%20discount%20amount.%26quot%3B%20However%2C%20that%20lack%20of%20consumer%20support%20has%20not%20stopped%20companies%20%E2%80%94%20insurers%20are%20starting%20to%20make%20such%20programs%20mandatory.%20For%20instance%2C%20health%20insurers%20can%20mandate%20employee%20participation%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatasociety.net%2Flibrary%2Fwellness-capitalism-employee-health-the-benefits-maze-and-worker-control%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecorporate%20wellness%20programs%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20track%20lifestyle%20data%2C%20and%20auto%20insurers%20can%20mandate%20smart%20devices%20in%20your%20vehicle%20if%20you've%20been%20deemed%20higher%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20direction%20the%20industry%20is%20heading%20is%20to%20use%20this%20flood%20of%20data%20to%20optimize%20pricing%20to%20the%20extent%20that%20your%20insurance%20policy%20is%20dynamic%20and%20constantly%20changing.%20For%20example%2C%20insurers%20are%20testing%20new%20business%20models%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.experian.com%2Fblogs%2Fask-experian%2Fwhat-is-on-demand-insurance%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eon-demand%20insurance%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20Rather%20than%20purchase%20an%20annual%20contract%20for%20something%20like%20car%20insurance%2C%20every%20time%20you%20drive%2C%20your%20insurance%20would%20activate%2C%20and%20when%20you%20aren't%20driving%2C%20it%20would%20deactivate.%20Each%20of%20these%20activations%20would%20be%20treated%20as%20a%20new%20transaction%20with%20a%20new%20contract%20%E2%80%94%20and%20a%20new%20price.%20Driving%20to%20get%20groceries%20on%20a%20sunny%20weekend%20morning%20might%20cost%20less%20than%2C%20say%2C%20picking%20up%20your%20kids%20during%20rush%20hour%20on%20a%20rainy%20evening.%20This%20emerging%20model%20is%20spreading%20as%20insurers%20experiment%20with%20new%20products%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgrist.org%2Fextreme-heat%2Fextreme-heat-is-here-can-insurance-help-protect-us%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esingle-day%20heat%20insurance%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20you%20can%20activate%20using%20a%20mobile%20app.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EColm%20Holmes%2C%20formerly%20the%20CEO%20of%20Aviva%20and%20now%20CEO%20of%20Allianz%20Holdings%20%E2%80%94%20both%20massive%20multinational%20insurers%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nsinsurance.com%2Fanalysis%2Faviva-colm-holmes-claims-inflation%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esummed%20up%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20problem%20with%20this%20model%20in%20a%202020%20interview%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20use%20of%20data%20is%20something%20I%20think%20regulators%20will%20have%20to%20look%20at%2C%20because%20if%20you%20get%20down%20to%20insuring%20the%20individual%2C%20you%20don't%20have%20an%20insurance%20industry%20%E2%80%94%20you%20just%20create%20people%20who%20don't%20need%20insurance%20and%20people%20who%20aren't%20insurable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHolmes%20is%20saying%20that%20the%20end%20result%20of%20this%20direction%20is%20that%20risky%20people%20lose%20their%20access%20to%20insurance%20while%20everyone%20else%20never%20needs%20to%20use%20their%20insurance%20%E2%80%94%20undermining%20the%20entire%20purpose%20of%20insurance%20as%20a%20way%20of%20collectively%20pooling%20risk.%20We're%20already%20seeing%20this%20as%20more%20people%20have%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcost-of-home-insurance-skyrocketing-crushing-homeowners-wildfires-flooding-storms-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehome-insurance%20policies%20canceled%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20claims%20denied.%20It%20could%20also%20mean%20endless%20profits%20for%20the%20companies%3A%20Millions%20of%20people%20pay%20in%2C%20while%20the%20insurer%20rarely%2C%20if%20ever%2C%20needs%20to%20pay%20out.%20To%20keep%20companies%20from%20becoming%20the%20architects%20of%20their%20own%20demise%20by%20pursuing%20that%20financial%20incentive%2C%20Holmes%20is%20saying%20that%20regulators%20need%20to%20step%20in%20to%20enforce%20limits.%20Otherwise%20we%20would%20have%20no%20real%20insurance%20to%20speak%20of.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ENickel%20and%20diming%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20her%20keynote%20during%20the%20recent%20International%20Congress%20of%20Actuaries%2C%20Inga%20Beale%2C%20the%20former%20CEO%20of%20the%20UK%20insurer%20Lloyd's%20of%20London%2C%20shared%20a%20story%20about%20trying%20to%20file%20a%20home-insurance%20claim%20after%20her%20roof%20had%20been%20damaged%20in%20a%20hailstorm.%20Beale's%20insurer%20had%20required%20her%20to%20get%20three%20independent%20quotes%20for%20repairs%2C%20fill%20out%20a%20stack%20of%20paperwork%2C%20engage%20in%20long%20interactions%20with%20a%20claims%20handler%2C%20and%20on%20and%20on.%20Eventually%2C%20Beale%20was%20so%20frustrated%20by%20the%20whole%20process%20that%20she%20decided%20to%20just%20pay%20for%20the%20repair%20herself.%20Beale%20was%20a%20professional%20underwriter%20in%20the%20highest%20echelon%20of%20the%20insurance%20industry%2C%20but%20she%20was%20also%20the%20victim%20of%20claims%20optimization%2C%20the%20insurance-industry%20practice%20where%20consumers%20are%20offered%20payouts%20not%20based%20on%20what%20they%20fairly%20deserve%20but%20based%20on%20what%20they%20are%20willing%20to%20accept.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20the%20freedom%20of%20retirement%2C%20Beale%20was%20taking%20aim%20at%20insurers'%20obsession%20with%20finding%20exclusions%20%E2%80%94%20that%20is%2C%20reasons%20not%20to%20underwrite%20risk%20or%20cover%20claims.%20She%20saw%20this%20as%20antithetical%20to%20the%20social%20purpose%20of%20insurance.%20What's%20the%20point%20of%20having%20insurers%20if%20they%20don't%20want%20to%20insure%20anything%20risky%3F%20Beale%20called%20these%20practices%20a%20systemic%20feature%20of%20an%20industry%20that%20has%20become%20too%20profit-oriented%20and%20risk-averse.%20I'll%20go%20even%20further%3A%20To%20boost%20their%20own%20profits%2C%20insurance%20companies%20are%20becoming%20increasingly%20antisocial%20and%20antagonistic.%20You%20may%20hate%20your%20insurer%2C%20but%20they%20probably%20hate%20you%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20possible%20way%20insurers%20limit%20how%20much%20they%20pay%20on%20claims%20is%20by%20simply%20paying%20less%20on%20a%20batch%20of%20claims%20and%20seeing%20how%20many%20customers%20complain.%20If%20the%20number%20of%20complaints%20doesn't%20reach%20a%20certain%20threshold%20%E2%80%94%20say%2C%205%25%20of%20claim%20decisions%20result%20in%20a%20formal%20complaint%20%E2%80%94%20then%20the%20amount%20paid%20is%20lowered%20even%20further%20with%20another%20batch%20of%20claims.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ethicsandinsurance.info%2Fclaims-complaints%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprocess%20of%20lowering%20payouts%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20can%20be%20automated%20by%20AI%20tools%2C%20is%20continued%20until%20that%20threshold%20of%20complaints%20is%20reached.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInsurers%20can%20also%20use%20their%20data-driven%20analysis%20of%20customers%20to%20predict%20who%20is%20prone%20to%20complain%20and%20preemptively%20offer%20them%20a%20fairer%20deal%20than%20those%20who%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20just%20accept%20what%20they%20are%20offered.%20Or%2C%20they%20can%20target%20customers%20with%20low%20credit%20scores%20%E2%80%94%20which%20indicates%20they%20might%20have%20money%20troubles%20and%20need%20cash%20right%20now%20%E2%80%94%20and%20offer%20them%20a%20quicker%2C%20no-hassle%20process%20in%20return%20for%20a%20reduced%20payout.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20dragging%20out%20claims%20until%20customers%20just%20give%20up%2C%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.propublica.org%2Farticle%2Fcigna-pxdx-medical-health-insurance-rejection-claims%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereporting%20by%20ProPublica%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20the%20health%20insurer%20Cigna%20uses%20a%20system%20that%20helps%20doctors%20instantly%20reject%20a%20claim%20on%20medical%20grounds%20without%20opening%20the%20patient%20file%2C%20forcing%20customers%20to%20go%20through%20a%20tortuous%20appeals%20process.%20%26quot%3BCigna%20adopted%20its%20review%20system%20more%20than%20a%20decade%20ago%2C%26quot%3B%20writes%20ProPublica%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20insurance%20executives%20say%20similar%20systems%20have%20existed%20in%20various%20forms%20throughout%20the%20industry.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOptimization%20is%20an%20industry%20euphemism%20for%20discrimination.%20Instead%20of%20drawing%20redlines%20around%20risky%20populations%20and%20deciding%20to%20charge%20them%20more%20and%20pay%20out%20less%2C%20insurers%20use%20automated%20systems%20to%20find%20patterns%20in%20data%20and%20optimize%20parameters%20for%20profitable%20risk%20management%20%E2%80%94%20which%20often%20has%20the%20same%20discriminatory%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearch%20by%20advocacy%20organizations%20in%20the%20UK%20has%20found%20strong%20evidence%20for%20discriminatory%20pricing%2C%20such%20as%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffairbydesign.com%2Finsurance-poverty-premium%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epoverty%20penalty%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.citizensadvice.org.uk%2Fabout-us%2Four-work%2Fpolicy%2Fpolicy-research-topics%2Fconsumer-policy-research%2Fconsumer-policy-research%2Fdiscriminatory-pricing-exploring-the-ethnicity-penalty-in-the-insurance-market1%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DWe%2520found%2520that%2520in%2520areas%2Cin%2520the%2520car%2520insurance%2520market.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eethnicity%20penalty%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.citizensadvice.org.uk%2Fcymraeg%2Famdanom-ni%2Four-work%2Fpolicy%2Fpolicy-research-topics%2Fconsumer-policy-research%2Fconsumer-policy-research%2Fexcessive-prices-for-disengaged-consumers-a-super-complaint-to-the-competition-and-markets-authority%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eloyalty%20penalty%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20where%20people%20are%20charged%20higher%20rates%20or%20refused%20coverage%20based%20on%20being%20poorer%2C%20living%20in%20communities%20of%20color%2C%20and%20sticking%20with%20one%20insurer%20rather%20than%20regularly%20shopping%20around%20and%20switching%20providers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20US%2C%20a%20class-action%20lawsuit%20against%20State%20Farm%20alleges%20that%20the%20company's%20use%20of%20automated%20platforms%20for%20handling%20claims%20resulted%20in%20racial%20discrimination%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2022%2F12%2F14%2Fbusiness%2Fstate-farm-racial-bias-lawsuit.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaying%20that%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3BBlack%20homeowners%20had%20a%20significantly%20harder%20time%20by%20several%20measures%26quot%3B%20to%20get%20their%20insurance%20claims%20approved%20compared%20to%20white%20homeowners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20State%20Farm%20spokesperson%20told%20The%20New%20York%20Times%3A%20%26quot%3BThis%20suit%20does%20not%20reflect%20the%20values%20we%20hold%20at%20State%20Farm.%20State%20Farm%20is%20committed%20to%20a%20diverse%20and%20inclusive%20environment%2C%20where%20all%20customers%20and%20associates%20are%20treated%20with%20fairness%2C%20respect%2C%20and%20dignity.%26quot%3B%20(A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcasetext.com%2Fcase%2Fhuskey-v-state-farm-fire-cas-co%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejudge%20denied%3C%2Fa%3E%20part%20of%20State%20Farm's%20motion%20for%20dismissal%2C%20ruling%20in%20September%20that%20the%20lawsuit%20can%20proceed%20with%20the%20plaintiff's%20claim%20of%20racial%20discrimination.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20kinds%20of%20practices%20that%20take%20advantage%20of%20consumers%20are%20intensified%20by%20the%20use%20of%20algorithmic%20systems%20designed%20to%20optimize%20profit%20for%20insurers%20by%20finding%20patterns%20across%20streams%20of%20data.%20Rather%20than%20making%20decisions%20on%20causality%20or%20objectivity%2C%20insurers%20depend%20upon%20correlation%20and%20interpretation.%20Their%20decisions%20are%20then%20laundered%20through%20the%20opacity%20of%20AI%2C%20giving%20insurers%20plausible%20deniability%20if%20their%20practices%20are%20determined%20unethical.%20If%20the%20machine%20is%20making%20the%20decisions%2C%20is%20anyone%20really%20at%20fault%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrivate%20insurers%20are%20not%20unique%20in%20succumbing%20to%20the%20financial%20imperatives%20of%20profit%20growth%2C%20but%20they%20are%20uniquely%20positioned%20to%20prey%20on%20our%20insecurities%2C%20exploit%20our%20desire%20for%20protection%2C%20and%20abandon%20us%20in%20our%20greatest%20times%20of%20need.%20And%20insurers%20hide%20behind%20the%20industry's%20reputation%20of%20being%20too%20boring%20to%20care%20about%2C%20too%20esoteric%20to%20understand%2C%20and%20too%20technical%20to%20challenge.%20But%20as%20insurance%20becomes%20more%20necessary%20and%20less%20accessible%20in%20the%20face%20of%20mounting%20risks%20from%20the%20climate%20crisis%2C%20we%20need%20to%20pay%20more%20critical%20attention%20to%20how%20insurers%20operate%20and%20whose%20best%20interests%20they%20really%20serve.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20crisis%20of%20insurance%20accessibility%20and%20rising%20costs%20cannot%20be%20fixed%20without%20real%20accountability%20and%20oversight%20of%20the%20industry.%20The%20stuff%20of%20insurance%20is%20far%20too%20important%20to%20be%20left%20to%20the%20insurance%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fjathan-sadowski%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EJathan%20Sadowski%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20Senior%20Research%20Fellow%20in%20the%20Faculty%20of%20Information%20Technology%20at%20Monash%20University.%20He%20co-hosts%20the%20podcast%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsoundcloud.com%2Fthismachinekillspod%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20Machine%20Kills%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0and%20wrote%20the%20book%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmitpress.mit.edu%2F9780262538589%2Ftoo-smart%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EToo%20Smart%3A%20How%20Digital%20Capitalism%20is%20Extracting%20Data%2C%20Controlling%20Our%20Lives%2C%20and%20Taking%20Over%20the%20World.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ECorrection%3A%20October%2023%2C%202023%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%94%20An%20earlier%20version%20of%20this%20story%20misstated%20how%20Cigna's%20system%20to%20process%20claims%20works.%20According%20to%20reporting%20from%20ProPublica%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cem%3Eit%20doesn't%20automatically%20reject%20claims%20under%20a%20set%20cost%2C%20it%20helps%20doctors%20instantly%20reject%20them%20without%20reviewing%20a%20patient's%20file.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsurance-companies-get-you-to-pay-more-deny-claims-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698054301000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65318e1996908fd7cdb31145%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsurance-companies-get-you-to-pay-more-deny-claims-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Home%2C%20health%2C%20and%20auto%20insurers%20are%20using%20creepy%20new%20technology%20to%20jack%20up%20your%20premiums%20and%20deny%20your%20claims.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Jathan%20Sadowski)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A58%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsurance-companies-get-you-to-pay-more-deny-claims-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22China%20has%20stolen%20more%20personal%20and%20corporate%20information%20than%20every%20other%20country%20in%20the%20world%20combined%2C%20FBI%20director%20says%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Christopher%20Wray%20(left)%20and%20China%20soldiers%20raising%20the%20flag%20(right).%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6535d9c40487ff031cab6f69%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BWe%20welcome%20business%20with%20China%2C%20visitors%20from%20China%2C%20academic%20exchange.%20What%20we%20don't%20welcome%20is%20cheating%2C%20and%20theft%2C%20and%20repression%2C%26quot%3B%20Christopher%20Wray%20told%2060%20Minutes'%20Scott%20Pelley.%3Cp%3EMark%20Wilson%20via%20Getty%20Images%3B%20Zhang%20Tao%2FXinhua%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3EFBI%20chief%20Christopher%20Wray%20says%20China%20is%20running%20the%20world's%20largest%20hacking%20program.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EHe%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbsnews.com%2Fnews%2Fchina-stealing-technology-secrets-five-eyes-intelligence-leaders-warn-60-minutes-transcript%2F%5C%22%3E60%20Minutes%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20China%20has%20stolen%20more%20US%20data%20%26quot%3Bthan%20every%20nation%2C%20big%20or%20small%2C%20combined.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EWray%20said%20China's%20espionage%20work%20could%20threaten%20the%20competitiveness%20of%20the%20US%20economy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EFBI%20Director%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffbi-director-somewhat-insane-to-suggest-hes-biased-against-conservatives-2023-7%5C%22%3EChristopher%20Wray%3C%2Fa%3E%20says%20China%20is%20running%20the%20world's%20most%20extensive%20hacking%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20have%20the%20biggest%20hacking%20program%20in%20the%20world%20by%20far%2C%20bigger%20than%20ever%20other%20major%20nation%20combined.%20Stolen%20more%20of%20our%20personal%20and%20corporate%20data%20than%20every%20nation%2C%20big%20or%20small%2C%20combined%2C%26quot%3B%20Wray%20told%2060%20Minutes'%20%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbsnews.com%2Fteam%2Fscott-pelley%2F%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%226c40e26aa045a6279bc373c155ba943a%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%2260%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbsnews.com%2Fteam%2Fscott-pelley%2F%5C%22%20data-analytics-product-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EScott%20Pelley%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbsnews.com%2Fnews%2Fchina-stealing-technology-secrets-five-eyes-intelligence-leaders-warn-60-minutes-transcript%2F%5C%22%3Einterview%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20aired%20on%20Sunday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWray%20was%20speaking%20during%20a%20joint%20interview%20with%20his%20counterparts%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dni.gov%2Findex.php%2Fncsc-how-we-work%2F217-about%2Forganization%2Ficig-pages%2F2660-icig-fiorc%5C%22%3EFive%20Eyes%3C%2Fa%3E%20intelligence%20alliance%2C%20a%20grouping%20that%20consists%20of%20the%20US%2C%20UK%2C%20Canada%2C%20Australia%2C%20and%20New%20Zealand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWray%20told%20Pelley%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecent-spy-case-shows-how-industrial-espionage-helps-chinese-military-2021-12%5C%22%3EChina's%20intelligence%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%20poses%20a%20significant%20threat%20to%20the%20US.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20first%20is%20that%20when%20people%20talk%20about%20stealing%20innovation%20or%20intellectual%20property%2C%20that's%20not%20just%20a%20Wall%20Street%20problem.%20That's%20a%20Main%20Street%20problem.%20That%20means%20American%20jobs%2C%20American%20families%2C%20American%20livelihoods%2C%20and%20the%20same%20thing%20for%20every%20one%20of%20our%20five%20countries%2C%20directly%20impacted%20by%20that%20theft%2C%26quot%3B%20Wray%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20some%20abstract%20concept.%20It%20has%20flesh%20and%20blood%2C%20kitchen-table%20consequences%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20continued.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Wray%20stopped%20short%20of%20saying%20that%20China%20is%20engaging%20in%20criminal%20activity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20seem%20to%20be%20saying%20that%20the%20Chinese%20government%20is%20running%20a%20criminal%20enterprise%2C%26quot%3B%20Pelley%20told%20Wray%20during%20the%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWell%2C%20I%20would%20say%20the%20Chinese%20government%2C%20if%20they%20want%20to%20be%20a%20great%20nation%2C%20it's%20time%20for%20them%20to%20start%20acting%20like%20one%2C%26quot%3B%20Wray%20said%20in%20response%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20Chinese%20government%20should%20work%20with%20other%20countries%20to%20combat%20common%20threats%20like%20drug%20trafficking%20and%20money%20laundering.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20means%20not%20working%20with%20criminals%20but%20rather%20working%20to%20uphold%20the%20rule%20of%20law%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20to%2060%20Minutes%2C%20China%20said%20it%20%26quot%3Bfirmly%20oppose%20the%20groundless%20allegations%20and%20smears%26quot%3B%20by%20the%20news%20program's%20interviewees.%2060%20Minutes%20did%20not%20specify%20which%20of%20China's%20ministries%20or%20agencies%20provided%20the%20comment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20and%20its%20allies%20have%20been%20fending%20off%20China's%20attempts%20at%20espionage.%20In%20February%2C%20the%20US%20military%20%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchinese-spy-balloon-synthetic-aperture-radar-discord-documents-pentagon-2023-4%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%22fd05cb24adc34b07f1cc3223b54c4475%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%22100%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchinese-spy-balloon-synthetic-aperture-radar-discord-documents-pentagon-2023-4%5C%22%20data-analytics-product-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%3Eshot%20down%20a%20Chinese%20surveillance%20balloon%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20it%20flew%20over%20the%20continental%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20June%2C%20%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fcuba-to-host-secret-chinese-spy-base-focusing-on-u-s-b2fed0e0%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow