%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20I%20work%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.calissahamptons.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECalissa%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20Greek%20fine-dining%20restaurant%20in%20Water%20Mill%2C%20Southampton%2C%20as%20a%20senior%20server%2C%20a%20captain%2C%20and%20a%20bartender.%20Calissa%20reached%20out%20and%20asked%20my%20husband%2C%20who's%20a%20chef%2C%20and%20me%20to%20interview%20together%20because%20we're%20year-round%20Hamptons%20residents%2C%20and%20they%20wanted%20to%20transition%20Calissa%20from%20a%20seasonal%20restaurant%20to%20a%20year-round%20restaurant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20both%20started%20in%20summer%202019%2C%20but%20when%20COVID-19%20hit%2C%20we%20were%20trying%20to%20figure%20out%20the%20best%20way%20to%20move%20forward%2C%20because%20without%20in-person%20dining%2C%20there%20are%20no%20tips.%20Management%20had%20discussed%20trying%20the%20no-tip%20model%20previously%2C%20but%20the%20pandemic%20was%20the%20catalyst.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECalissa%20started%20using%20this%20model%20in%202020%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECalissa%20decided%20to%20add%20an%2018%25%20service-administration%20fee%20to%20all%20checks%2C%20including%20to-go%20orders%2C%20in%20March%202020.%20They%20also%20raised%20our%20hourly%20wages%20from%20%2410%20an%20hour%20to%20between%20about%20%2425%20and%20%2450%20an%20hour%2C%20depending%20on%20seniority%20and%20other%20factors.%20I%20make%20closer%20to%20the%20top%20end%20of%20the%20rate%20because%20of%20my%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeing%20an%20hourly%20employee%20has%20been%20amazing.%20It's%20made%20my%20life%20so%20much%20easier%20knowing%20what%20I'll%20make.%20I%20don't%20have%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20stress%20of%20squirreling%20away%20the%20higher%20tips%20I%20make%20over%20the%20summer%20to%20make%20it%20through%20the%20winter.%20Even%20though%20my%20hours%20go%20down%20in%20the%20winter%20from%2038%20to%2028%20hours%2C%20knowing%20exactly%20what%20I'll%20earn%20is%20invaluable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESome%20customers%20still%20tip%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOccasionally%2C%20customers%20still%20tip%20even%20though%20the%20restaurant%20lists%20the%20administration%20fee%20on%20the%20menus%2C%20the%20website%2C%20and%20the%20checks.%20It's%20usually%20nominal%20%E2%80%94%20an%20extra%20%245%20or%20an%20extra%20%2410%20%E2%80%94%20but%20occasionally%2C%20customers%20are%20so%20happy%20they'll%20throw%20in%20an%20extra%20%2450.%20The%20restaurant%20then%20distributes%20that%20money%20to%20all%20front-of-house%20employees%3A%20captains%2C%20servers%2C%20back%20waiters%2C%20runners%2C%20barbacks%2C%20and%20bartenders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20never%20a%20ton%20of%20money%2C%20but%20we%20greatly%20appreciate%20it%3B%20they're%20giving%20you%20an%20extra%20pat%20on%20the%20back%20because%20they're%20impressed%20with%20your%20service.%20We%20always%20try%20to%20elevate%20our%20service%20so%20customers%20feel%20the%20administration%20fee%20is%20worth%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETypically%2C%20I%20make%20about%20%2475%20to%20%24150%20a%20week%20on%20top%20of%20the%20hourly%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHaving%20a%20husband%2C%20a%20child%2C%20and%20a%20mortgage%20means%20this%20model%20is%20a%20godsend%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20no%20longer%20crossing%20my%20fingers%2C%20hoping%20for%20generous%20customers%20who%20spend%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20or%20order%20a%20nice%20bottle%20of%20wine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%2C%20if%20someone%20came%20in%20for%20a%20chat%20and%20just%20a%20few%20glasses%20of%20wine%2C%20that%20wasn't%20great.%20On%20a%20%2470%20check%2C%20hopefully%20I%20would%20get%20tipped%20%2414.%20But%20if%20they%20ordered%20appetizers%2C%20entr%C3%A9es%2C%20and%20desserts%2C%20the%20check%20would%20now%20be%20%24250%2C%20and%20I'd%20get%20%2450.%20This%20no-tip%20model%20takes%20away%20all%20that%20uncertainty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20worked%20with%20people%20who%20stressed%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20month%2C%20saying%20things%20including%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20didn't%20make%20any%20money%20this%20month%2C%20and%20my%20car%20payment%20is%20due%20in%20a%20couple%20of%20days%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BI%20have%20to%20pay%20my%20babysitter%20tonight%2C%20but%20I%20didn't%20make%20anything%20and%20have%20no%20cash%20to%20pay.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThanks%20to%20my%20reliable%20income%2C%20I%20was%20fortunate%20to%20have%20saved%20enough%20for%20a%2012-day%20trip%20to%20Italy%20with%20the%20family%20this%20year%2C%20where%20they%20also%20don't%20have%20a%20tipping%20model.%20I%20still%20left%20a%20few%20euros%20on%20the%20table%20at%20restaurants%20as%20a%20gesture%20of%20appreciation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20plan%20on%20staying%20at%20Calissa%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20is%20now%20the%20executive%20chef%2C%20and%20I'm%20happy%20to%20be%20working%20for%20a%20company%20with%20this%20model%20in%20place.%20The%20restaurant%20doesn't%20have%20plans%20to%20go%20back%20to%20a%20tipping%20model%20now%20that%20pandemic%20restrictions%20have%20eased%20because%20both%20employees%20and%20management%20are%20happy%20with%20what's%20currently%20in%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frestaurant-got-rid-of-tips-eliminated-tipping-server-living-wage-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698052201000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65329b7796908fd7cdb3c215%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frestaurant-got-rid-of-tips-eliminated-tipping-server-living-wage-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20restaurant%20eliminated%20tipping%20and%20now%20pays%20its%20workers%20a%20living%20wage.%20The%20model%20has%20made%20a%20server's%20life%20in%20the%20Hamptons%20more%20comfortable%20all%20year.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Kaila%20Yu)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A