%20%3Cp%3ESarma%20had%20first%20written%20to%20the%20ECI%20on%20October%2021%2C%20saying%20that%20the%20commission%20must%20intervene%20and%20block%20this%20government%20order.%20These%20instructions%2C%20he%20argued%2C%20were%20against%20the%20model%20code%20of%20conduct.%20Former%20IAS%20officer%20M.G.%20Devasahayam%20had%20endorsed%20Sarma%E2%80%99s%20letter.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20second%20letter%20sent%20on%20Monday%20(October%2023)%2C%20Sarma%20said%20he%20hoped%20the%20ECI%20had%20taken%20cognisance%20of%20his%20complaint.%20He%20pointed%20out%20four%20relating%20issues%2C%20including%20saying%20that%20public%20servants%20engaging%20in%20this%20kind%20of%20activity%20had%20the%20power%20to%20influence%20voters%20and%20electoral%20outcomes.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20ECI%2C%20Sarma%20argued%2C%20had%20a%20duty%20to%20act%20on%20the%20matter.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20the%20Commission%20fails%20to%20discharge%20its%20responsibilities%20envisaged%20under%20Article%20324%20and%20the%20relevant%20election%20laws%2C%20it%20will%20undoubtedly%20amount%20to%20causing%20irreparable%20damage%20to%20the%20democratic%20values%20that%20lie%20at%20the%20core%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERead%20his%20full%20letter%20below.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EE%20A%20S%20Sarma%3Cbr%3E%20Former%20Secretary%20to%20the%20Government%20of%20India%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETo%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EShri%20Rajiv%20Kumar%3Cbr%3E%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%3Cbr%3E%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20(ECI)%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EShri%20A%20C%20Pandey%3Cbr%3E%20Election%20Commissioner%3Cbr%3E%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20(ECI)%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EShri%20Arun%20Goel%3Cbr%3E%20Election%20Commissioner%3Cbr%3E%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20(ECI)%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDear%20S%2FShri%20Rajiv%20Kumar%2F%20Pandey%2F%20Goel%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EI%20write%20this%20in%20continuation%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcountercurrents.org%2F2023%2F10%2Fdifferent-ministries-of-the-central-government-have-possibly-infringed-the-model-code-of-conduct%2F%5C%22%3Emy%20letter%20of%20October%2021%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20which%20I%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20instructions%20issued%20by%20the%20Department%20of%20Personnel%2C%20vide%20F.no.%201-28047%2F8%2F2023%20dated%2017-10-2023%20and%20other%20Ministries%20to%20nominate%20senior%20officers%20as%20%E2%80%9CDistrict%20Rath%20Praharis%E2%80%9D%20under%20their%20purview%20to%20%E2%80%9C%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3Eshowcase%2Fcelebrate%20achievements%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3Eof%20the%20NDA%20government%20during%20the%20last%20nine%20years%20through%20%E2%80%98Viksit%20Bharat%20Sankalp%20Yatra%E2%80%99%C2%A0from%2020th%20November%202023%20to%2025th%20January%202024%E2%80%B3%2C%20on%20the%20eve%20of%20the%20State%20Assembly%20elections%2C%20brazenly%20violate%20the%C2%A0Model%20Code%20of%20Conduct%20(MCC)%20for%20those%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EI%20hope%20that%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20(ECI)%20has%20taken%20due%20cognizance%20of%20my%20complaint%20and%20acted%20as%20it%20should%2C%20as%20an%20independent%20authority%20under%20the%20Constitution%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20said%20elections%20are%20conducted%20in%20a%20free%20and%20fair%20manner.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20related%20issues%2C%20as%20indicated%20below%2C%20on%20which%20I%20would%20call%20upon%20the%20ECI%20to%20act%20immediately%20and%C2%A0unhesitatingly.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E1.%20Public%20servants%20taking%20part%20in%20any%20activity%20that%20is%20likely%20to%20influence%20the%20voters%20in%20an%20election%20violates%20the%20Central%20Civil%20Services%20(Conduct)%20Rules%20and%20the%20corresponding%20conduct%20rules%20of%20the%20other%20Central%20and%20All%20India%20Services.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E2.%20Under%20Section%20171C%20of%20the%20IPC%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Ewhoever%20voluntarily%20interferes%20or%20attempts%20to%20interfere%20with%20the%20free%20exercise%20of%20any%20electoral%20right%20commits%20the%20offence%20of%20undue%20influence%20at%20an%20election%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9C.%C2%A0%C2%A0For%20any%20public%20authority%20to%20coerce%20public%20servants%20into%20such%20activity%20is%20punishable%20not%20only%20under%20the%20relevant%20election%20laws%20but%20also%20under%20the%20relevant%20provisions%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20(IPC)%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E3.%20The%20Government%20of%20India%2C%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%20Office%20Memorandum%20No.25%2F44%2F49%2FEsts.%20dated%2010th%20October%201949%20states%2C%C2%A0%C2%A0%E2%80%9C%20%3Cem%3EAttention%20is%20invited%20to%20the%20scope%20of%20Rule%2023(I)%20of%20the%20Government%20Servants%E2%80%99%20Conduct%20Rules%20which%20lays%20down%20that%20no%20Government%20servant%20shall%20take%20part%20in%2C%20subscribe%20in%20aid%20or%20assist%20in%20any%20way%2C%20any%20political%20movement%20in%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9C.%20These%20instructions%20assume%20particular%20relevance%20in%20relation%20to%20the%20concern%20expressed%20by%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E4.%20At%20least%20four%20Union%20Ministers%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Felections%2Flok-sabha%2Findia%2F18-mps-including-4-union-ministers-bjps-star-studded-lineup-for-state-showdowns%2Farticleshow%2F104290879.cms%5C%22%3Ereported%20to%20be%20contesting%20the%20ensuing%20State%20assembly%20elections%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Deploying%20Central%20government%20officers%20in%20activity%20that%20amounts%20to%20canvassing%20for%20the%20ruling%20political%20parties%20in%20elections%20they%20are%20contesting%20would%20clearly%20attract%20disqualification%20under%20the%20relevant%20provisions%20of%20the%20election%20laws%2C%20which%20the%20ECI%20should%20examine%20urgently.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20precedent%20set%20by%20the%20Central%20government%20by%20issuing%20the%20said%20instructions%20to%20its%20officers%20to%C2%A0%E2%80%9C%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3Eshowcase%2Fcelebrate%20achievements%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3Eof%20the%20NDA%20government%20during%20the%20last%20nine%20years%20through%20%E2%80%98Viksit%20Bharat%20Sankalp%20Yatra'%E2%80%9D%20is%20likely%20to%20incentivise%20the%20political%20leadership%20in%20each%20State%20that%20will%20go%20for%20Assembly%20elections%20shortly%20to%20do%20likewise%20and%20instruct%20its%20own%20officers%20to%20canvass%20for%20them%2C%20leading%20to%20anarchy%20and%20erosion%20of%20democratic%20values%20that%20are%20central%20to%20the%20electoral%20system%20envisaged%20in%20our%20Constitution.%20The%20Commission%20cannot%20afford%20to%20remain%20passive%20and%20become%20an%20abettor%20of%20such%20a%20potentially%20dangerous%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMay%20I%20call%20upon%20the%20ECI%20to%20act%20urgently%20on%20these%20concerns%20and%20act%20without%20hesitation%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20no%20political%20party%20gets%20an%20undue%20advantage%20in%20the%20ensuing%20State%20Assembly%20elections%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20Commission%20fails%20to%20discharge%20its%20responsibilities%20envisaged%20under%20Article%20324%20and%20the%20relevant%20election%20laws%2C%20it%20will%20undoubtedly%20amount%20to%20causing%20irreparable%20damage%C2%A0to%20the%20democratic%20values%20that%20lie%20at%20the%20core%20of%20the%20Constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EI%20am%20circulating%20this%20letter%20widely%20for%20the%20public%20to%20discuss%20and%20debate%20the%20above%20concerns%20and%20the%20role%20that%20the%20Commission%20ought%20to%20play%20as%20an%C2%A0independent%20Constitutional%20authority.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERegards%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EYours%20sincerely%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EE%20A%20S%20Sarma%3Cbr%3E%20Visakhapatnam%3Cbr%3E%2023-10-2023%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698051615000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F27124559%2FF64MDKrXYAAbRfI.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Feas-sarma-letter-eci-rath-prabharis%22%2C