oned%20and%20completed%20over%20his%20previous%20terms%20and%20his%20reputation%20for%20growth%20and%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20clearly%20attempted%20to%20put%20himself%20between%20the%20electorate%20and%20the%20Shehbaz%20Sharif%20government%E2%80%99s%20abysmal%20performance%20%E2%80%93%20its%20various%20constraints%20notwithstanding%20%E2%80%93%20during%20which%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fasia.nikkei.com%2FEconomy%2FInflation%2FPakistan-inflation-hits-record-35-as-IMF-talks-drag-on%5C%22%3Einflation%20had%20risen%20to%2035%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Pakistan%20narrowly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2023-07-12%2Fpakistan-secures-final-imf-approval-for-3-billion-bailout%23xj4y7vzkg%5C%22%3Edodged%20the%20economic%20default%20bullet%3C%2Fa%3E.%20While%20he%20bragged%20about%20making%20Pakistan%20a%20declared%20nuclear-weapons%20state%2C%20he%20also%20reiterated%20%E2%80%93%20without%20naming%20India%20%E2%80%93%20that%20there%20can%20be%20no%20progress%20while%20fighting%20the%20neighbors.%20It%20was%20indeed%20heartening%20to%20see%20Sharif%2C%20who%20is%20seen%20as%20close%20to%20the%20Israel-friendly%20Saudis%20and%20the%20UAE%2C%20wave%20a%20Palestinian%20flag%20on%20the%20stage%20at%20a%20time%20when%20many%20world%20leaders%20have%20shied%20away%20from%20raising%20their%20voice%20against%20the%20war%20in%20Gaza.%20For%20a%20first%20rally%20and%20speech%20after%20a%20four-year%20interregnum%2C%20Nawaz%20Sharif%20did%20achieve%20what%20he%20had%20set%20out%20to%20do%3A%20energize%20and%20mobilize%20his%20base%2C%20especially%20the%20Punjab.%20But%20the%20nostalgic%20broad%20strokes%20and%20reconciliatory%20notes%20can%20only%20be%20used%20a%20few%20times%20before%20they%20run%20out%20of%20their%20political%20efficacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENawaz%20Sharif%20will%20have%20to%20tackle%20both%20the%20economic%20and%20political%20future%20of%20Pakistan%20and%20define%20and%20refine%20the%20roadmap%2C%20if%20he%20has%20any.%20There%20are%20no%20easy%20solutions%20out%20of%20the%20economic%20morass%20the%20country%20remains%20in%20despite%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftribune.com.pk%2Fstory%2F2440482%2Fimf-sticks-to-25-growth-forecast-for-pakistan%5C%22%3Eslightly%20better%20forecast%20from%20the%20IMF%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20political%20rancor%20of%20the%20past%205%20years%20continues%20to%20loom%20large.%20Sharif%20did%20not%20name%20Imran%20Khan%20even%20once%20in%20his%20speech%2C%20but%20it%20would%20be%20interesting%20to%20see%20how%20he%20addresses%20the%20issue%20of%20his%20archrival%E2%80%99s%20incarceration%20and%20potential%20elimination%20from%20the%20next%20elections.%20Despite%20an%20imprisoned%20Imran%20Khan%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nation.com.pk%2F22-Sep-2023%2Fdurrani-active-for-reconciliation-between-pti-authoritative-elements%5C%22%3Edesperately%20seeking%20a%20reconciliation%20with%20the%20army%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20latter%20is%20unlikely%20to%20be%20forgiving%20anytime%20soon.%20An%20election%20held%20without%20Imran%20Khan%2C%20however%2C%20would%20be%20as%20tainted%20as%20the%20one%20that%20was%20held%20without%20Nawaz%20Sharif%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20PML-N%20has%20fielded%20Nawaz%20Sharif%20effectively%20as%20its%20prime%20ministerial%20candidate%2C%20were%20it%20to%20prevail%20in%20the%20general%20elections%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dawn.com%2Fnews%2F1782740%2Fnawaz-moves-to-restore-appeals-against-convictions%5C%22%3Elegal%20status%20of%20his%20previous%20disqualification%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20electoral%20process%20is%20still%20not%20completely%20clear.%20But%20all%20indications%20are%20that%20the%20army%20would%20not%20create%20any%20hurdles%20in%20his%20way.%20One%20speech%20is%20not%20much%20to%20go%20by%2C%20but%20it%20is%20unlikely%20that%20Nawaz%20Sharif%20will%20do%20the%20army%E2%80%99s%20bidding%20were%20he%20to%20return%20to%20power%20a%20fourth%20time.%20Opting%20for%20reticence%20and%20restraint%20vis-%C3%A0-vis%20the%20former%20generals%20and%20judges%20appears%20to%20be%20a%20tactical%20move%20on%20Sharif%E2%80%99s%20part.%20With%20the%20army%E2%80%99s%20most%20recent%20encroachment%20over%20the%20political%20domain%20it%20is%20more%20likely%20than%20ever%20before%20that%20a%20PM%20Nawaz%20Sharif%20will%20eventually%20lock%20horns%20with%20an%20army%20chief%2C%20whether%20the%20incumbent%20or%20a%20successor.%20It%20is%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20principals%2C%20positions%2C%20and%20politics%20that%20define%20the%20interplay%20between%20the%20PMs%20and%20the%20army%20chiefs%20in%20Pakistan.%20Militaries%20are%20not%20trained%20to%20run%20complex%20states%20and%20the%20very%20nature%20of%20a%20constitutional%20democracy%20%E2%80%93%20even%20a%20weak%20one%20like%20Pakistan%E2%80%94puts%20the%20brass%20at%20loggerheads%20with%20the%20%3Cem%3Ede%20jure%3C%2Fem%3E%20chief%20executives.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20historical%20lesson%20is%20that%20even%20the%20weakest%20prime%20ministers%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.latimes.com%2Farchives%2Fla-xpm-1988-05-30-mn-2462-story.html%5C%22%3EMuhammad%20Khan%20Junejo%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Farchive%2Fpolitics%2F2004%2F06%2F27%2Fpakistani-premier-forced-out-in-favor-of-finance-minister%2F68680c3c-3c33-4e2e-995f-d3742dac01f0%2F%5C%22%3EMir%20Zafarullah%20Khan%20Jamali%3C%2Fa%3E%20ended%20up%20having%20differences%20with%20the%20strongest%20army%20dictators%2C%20General%20Ziaul%20Haq%20and%20General%20Musharraf%2C%20respectively.%20Nawaz%20Sharif%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20is%20cut%20from%20a%20very%20different%20cloth.%20He%20had%20tried%20to%20assert%20his%20constitutional%20authority%20every%20single%20time%20he%20occupied%20the%20PM%E2%80%99s%20office%20in%20the%20past%2C%20though%20at%20his%20personal%20and%20political%20peril.%20And%20there%20is%20little%20reason%20to%20believe%20that%20it%20would%20be%20different